'''''Brain Games''''' is a [[popular science]] [[television series]] that explores [[cognitive science]] by focusing on [[illusion]]s, [[psychological experiment]]s, and [[counterintuitive]] thinking. [[Neil Patrick Harris]] was the unseen narrator in the first season, replaced by [[Jason Silva]] for the remainder of the series as its host and presenter; in addition, [[sleight-of-hand]] artist [[Apollo Robbins]] has been a frequent consultant and illusionist guest on the show. The show is interactive, encouraging television viewers, often along with a handful of live volunteers, to engage in visual, auditory, and other cognitive experiments, or "brain games", that emphasize the main points presented in each episode. The series debuted on the [[National Geographic Channel]] in 2011 as a special.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brain Games - About|url=http://natgeotv.com/uk/brain-games/about|publisher=Nat Geo|year=2013|accessdate=8 July 2013}}</ref>  Its return as an original series in 2013 set a record for the highest premiere rating for any National Geographic Channel original series with 1.5 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tv-ratings-brain-games-premiere-444723|title=TV Ratings: 'Brain Games' Premiere Sets Nat Geo Record|last=O'Connell|first=Michael|date=April 23, 2013|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=March 21, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321174311/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tv-ratings-brain-games-premiere-444723|archivedate=March 21, 2015}}</ref> Season 7 aired in 2016. National Geographic announced that the show would return as a 2-hour live event in the fall of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://renewcanceltv.com/brain-games-renewed-for-season-8-as-live-event/|title=Brain Games Renewed For Season 8 As Live Event!|date=18 April 2018|publisher=}}</ref>

The series is deemed acceptable for use toward [[E/I]] credits, and [[Litton Entertainment]] added repurposed reruns of the show to its ''[[One Magnificent Morning]]'' block in fall 2017.<ref name="OMM2017-18">{{cite news|title=The CW Announces Fall 2017 'One Magnificent Morning' Saturday Morning Line-Up|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/The-CW-Announces-Fall-2017-One-Magnificent-Morning-Saturday-Morning-Line-Up-20170913|accessdate=September 13, 2017|work=TV News Desk|publisher=Broadway World|date=September 13, 2017}}</ref>

